Peanut Butter Balls
  --Grandma Tosh

1 c butter
2 c chunky peanut butter
1 lb package powdered sugar
3 c rice krispies

Combine above ingredients until thoroughly blended. Shape into walnut sized balls.

Melt in double boiler:
1 hersgey's chocolate bar
6 oz chocolate chips
1/2 bar parawax

Dip balls into chocolate mixture with tongs. Put on wax paper; let sit until chocolate is hard.


Notes: Recipes by Grandma Tosh are written as close to what she wrote as possible.
I use dark chocolate and cocoa butter melted together, then tempered
